# {{.ProjectName}}

Codex package scaffold generated by [plugin-kit-ai](https://github.com/777genius/plugin-kit-ai) `init`.

This lane models the official Codex plugin bundle only.

## Status

- Package lane: `codex-package`
- Status: `production-ready` package contract
- Launcher: not used

## First Run

```bash
plugin-kit-ai render .
plugin-kit-ai render --check .
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform codex-package --strict
```

## Target Files

- `targets/codex-package/package.yaml`: first-class Codex package metadata (`author`, `homepage`, `repository`, `license`, `keywords`)
- `targets/codex-package/interface.json`: optional structured Codex `interface` doc rendered into `.codex-plugin/plugin.json`; the starter uses the documented `defaultPrompt` array shape
- `targets/codex-package/manifest.extra.json`: passthrough only for unsupported future Codex manifest fields; canonical package/interface fields stay managed
- `mcp/servers.yaml`: optional portable MCP authored source; `plugin-kit-ai init --extras` pre-seeds a starter and render projects it into managed `.mcp.json` plus `.codex-plugin/plugin.json#mcpServers`
- `targets/codex-package/app.json`: optional Codex app manifest copied to `.app.json`; the starter stays ignored until you replace the empty placeholder with a real app manifest
- `.codex-plugin/plugin.json`: rendered managed Codex plugin manifest

Use this lane for skills, MCP, interface/app metadata, and marketplace-ready package output.
